      "type": "understanding",
      "summary": "Agent explained goal and mechanics.",
      "understanding": {
        "goal_understanding": "The goal is to navigate a grid-based puzzle, collect or activate modifier tiles to match the required shape, color, and rotation of one or more goal cells, then step onto those goal cells to complete them. All goals in a level must be completed to advance. Stamina management is crucial, as running out costs lives, and losing all lives ends the game.",
        "mechanics_understanding": "Each turn, the player can move north, south, east, or west, consuming 1 stamina per move. Walls block movement; attempting a blocked direction wastes stamina. Modifier tiles change the player's piece: shape changers cycle the shape, color changers cycle the color in a fixed order (orange\u2192blue\u2192green\u2192red\u2192orange), and rotation changers rotate the piece 90\u00b0 clockwise (0\u00b0\u219290\u00b0\u2192180\u00b0\u2192270\u00b0\u21920\u00b0). A goal cell becomes active only when the carried piece's shape, color, and rotation all match its requirements. Once active, stepping onto it completes the goal. Stamina refills may exist. Losing all stamina costs a life and resets stamina; losing all lives triggers game over."
      }
